.TH "zbud_map" 9 "zbud_map" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
zbud_map \- maps the allocation associated with the given handle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" zbud_map
.BI "(struct zbud_pool *pool "  ","
.BI "unsigned long handle "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pool" 12
pool in which the allocation resides
.IP "handle" 12
handle associated with the allocation to be mapped
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
While trivial for zbud, the mapping functions for others allocators
implementing this allocation API could have more complex information encoded
in the handle and could create temporary mappings to make the data
accessible to the user.
.SH "RETURN"
a pointer to the mapped allocation
